archive/movie/summer-of-love.html Summer of Love], Schwarz Foundation, curated by Katerina Gregos, Lesbos, GR\n*2017 [https://www.dedomijnen.nl/tentoonstellingen/expositie/ben-ik-een-dier/ Ben ik een dier?] De Domijnen, Sittard, NL\n*2017 [https://www.cbkzeeland.nl/kunst/fa-ade-2017 CBK Zeeland], FA\u00c7ADE 2017: Face your freedom, Zeeland, NL \n*2017 Screen Present Tense, HDLU, Zagreb\n*2017 [https://www.leopoldmuseum.org/en/exhibitions/90/the-conundrum-of-imagination Wiener Festwochen - The Conundrum of Imagination], Leopold Museum Vienna, AU\n*2017 Bienne Festival of Photography, Biel, CH\n*2017 Planetary Garden, curated by Ashley Lumb & Laura Mclean, Manuka Arts Centre, AU\n*2017 [http://archive.artefact-festival.be/2017/en/program/artefact-expo-act-magic.html Artefact Expo: The Act of Magic], curated by Karen Verschooren & Ilse Huygens, STUK, Leuven, BE\n*2017 Living in Dreams, curated by Els Fiers & Frank Koolen, De Bond Brugge, BE\n*2016 Give Me Yesterday, Fondazione Prada, IT [http://www.fondazioneprada.org/project/give-me-yesterday/?lang=en]\n*2016 Close-Up A New Generation of Film and Video Artists in the Netherlands [https://www.eyefilm.nl/en/exhibition/close-up-%E2%80%93-a-new-generation-of-film-and-video-artists-in-the-netherlands], [[EYE Film Institute Netherlands|EYE Film Institute]], Amsterdam \n*2016 Hacking Habitat, NL [https://www.hackinghabitat.com/nl/persoon/melanie-bonajo/]\n\n==Awards==\n*2019 Prix Pictet (nominee)\n*2018 Amsterdamprijs voor de Kunst (nominee)\n*2018 Nam June Paik Award (nominee)\n*2017 Prix de Rome (nominee)\n*2017 Campaign Artist for Amsterdam Unseen \n*2016 Shortlisted for the Dutch Pavilion at the 57th Venice Biennale\n*2015 IFFR Tiger Award for short films (nominee) \n*2014 IFFR Tiger Award for short films (nominee) \n*2013 MK Award \n*2011 C.o.C.a (nominee)\n*2009 [[Prins Bernhard Cultuurfonds]], Peter Paul Peterich Fonds \n*2009 Festival Internationale de la Mode et Photographie \n*2007 PUP Award \n*2006 Berlinale Talent Campus\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160617033008/https://vimeo.com/118306379 Melanie Bonajo] on [[Vimeo]]\n* https://web.archive.org/web/20160514020229/http://lightra.com/front/gallery/40\n* http://www.doitwithothers.nl/projecten/melanie-bonajo/\n* http://artforum.com/words/id=48546\n* http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/13/artists-respond-female-body-censorship-online_n_7042926.html\n* the \"anti-selfie\" crying pictures http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/09/15/melanie-bonajo_n_5811496.html\n* http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/gallery/18284/6/capricious-day-melanie-bonajo \n* http://www.akinci.nl/Bonajo/Melanie%20Bonajo.htm\n* https://web.archive.org/web/20171107031038/http://www.mistermotley.nl/en/art-everyday-life/melanie-meets-bianca-casady\n* http://www.stedelijk.nl/agenda/gallery-talks/isa-genzken-door-de-ogen-van-melanie-bonajo\n* http://www.e-flux.com/announcements/2016-cinema-programme/\n* http://bombmagazine.org/article/1000294/kim-hiorth-y\n* http://www.doitwithothers.nl/category/melanie-bonajo/\n* http://bedfordandbowery.com/2016/05/will-the-actors-in-icaros-a-vision-win-ayahu-oscars-for-their-on-set-tripping/\n* http://artforum.com/diary/id=59667\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bonajo, Melanie}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Feminist artists]]\n[[Category:Dutch performance artists]]\n[[Category:Dutch women photographers]]\n[[Category:Women installation artists]]\n[[Category:People from Heerlen]]\n[[Category:Gerrit Rietveld Academie alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century women artists]]\n[[Category:Dutch contemporary artists]]\n", "text_old": "'''Melanie Bonajo''' (born 13 November 1978, [[Heerlen]])<ref>[https://rkd.nl/explore/artists/249380 Melanie Bonajo] at the [[RKD]]</ref> is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] artist working with film, performance, installations, music, event organizing, and photography. Her works address themes of eroding intimacy and isolation in an increasingly sterile, technological world.<ref>Frank, Priscilla. [http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/09/15/melanie-bonajo_n_5811496.html \"Meet The High Priestess Of The Anti-Selfie, Dutch Artist Melanie Bonajo\"], \"[[Huffington Post]]\", 2 November 2015. Retrieved on 7 April 2016.</ref> Her experimental documentaries often explore communities living or working on the margins of society, either through illegal means or cultural exclusion. Her work has been exhibited and screened internationally, from the [[Tate Modern]], [[MoMA PS1]], to [[De Appel]] Arts Centre and [[Stedelijk Museum Amsterdam|Stedelijk Museum]] in Amsterdam to the Center for Contemporary Art, Warsaw, the [[Kunsthalle Basel]], [[International Documentary Film Festival]] (IDFA), the [[Berlin International Film Festival|Berlinale]], the [[International Film Festival Rotterdam]], and Treefort Film Fest.<ref>[http://www.stedelijk.nl/agenda/gallery-talks/isa-genzken-door-de-ogen-van-melanie-bonajo \"Isa Genzken Door De Ogen Van Melanie Bonajo - Stedelijk Museum Amsterdam.\"] 1 January 2016. Retrieved 7 April 2016.</ref>\n\n==Notable work== \nBonajo's film series ''Night Soil'' is a trio of experimental documentaries about modern approaches to nature and the cultural implications of acting against capitalism. The first in the series, ''Night Soil - Fake Paradise'', is about psychedelic plant medication and human-plant conversations.<ref>Yoshimura, Courtney. [http://artforum.com/words/id=48546 \"Melanie Bonajo Speaks about Her New Video at the De Appel Arts Centre\"] \"[[ArtForum]]\", 8 October 2014. Retrieved 7 April 2016.</ref> The sequel, ''Night Soil - Economy of Love'' presents an alternative ethical model for sex-work healing and activism. The third film, \"Night Soil - Nocturnal Gardening\" questions the role of radical agriculture in a world of dwindling natural resources and disconnection to nature. Her  other recent film, which premiered at Hacking Habitat, ''Progress vs. Regress'' is the first in a trilogy that questions how technology has evolved through the eyes of elderly people in the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hacking Habitat|title=Melanie Bonajo|url=https://www.hackinghabitat.com/nl/persoon/melanie-bonajo/|accessdate=September 18, 2016|date=2016}}</ref> This film was also selected for [[International Documentary Film Festival Amsterdam|IDFA]] (International Documentary Film Festival Amsterdam) 2016<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.idfa.nl/industry/tags/project.aspx?id=3A3E049B-BD39-4B4F-AE4E-90A6BD25F59D&tab=idfa |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-11-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161107222606/https://www.idfa.nl/industry/tags/project.aspx?id=3A3E049B-BD39-4B4F-AE4E-90A6BD25F59D&tab=idfa |archivedate=2016-11-07 }}</ref>\n\n==Music and Performance==\nBonajo has performed internationally at venues such as [[Paradiso (Amsterdam)|Paradiso]] in Amsterdam, Baby's Alright in NYC and Coll\u00e8ge des Bernardins in Paris alongside artists such as [[Kembra Pfahler]] and Bianca Cassidy of [[CocoRosie]].<ref>Bonajo, Melanie. [http://www.mistermotley.nl/en/art-everyday-life/melanie-meets-bianca-casady \"MELANIE MEETS BIANCA CASADY\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107031038/http://www.mistermotley.nl/en/art-everyday-life/melanie-meets-bianca-casady |date=2017-11-07 }} 28 July 2014. Retrieved 7 April 2016.</ref> Her band, ZaZaZoZo,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/ZaZaZoZo-229220367171954/|title=ZaZaZoZo|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> is a music project with Joseph Marzolla known for its tribal pop sound and animalistic influence.<ref>Bonajo, Melanie. [http://bombmagazine.org/article/1000294/kim-hiorth-y \"Kim Hiorth\u00f8y by Melanie Bonajo\"], \"[[BOMB Magazine]]\", 29 October 2014. Retrieved 7 April 2016.</ref> All their music is produced by Bonajo's brother Tommie Bonajo at his Tomster studios. They released their debut album ''INUA'' in spring 2013 by ''Tsunami Addiction''. Their latest single and video, ''Woke up as a Wolf'', was released in 2014.\n\n==Feminism== \nBonajo's ''Furniture Bondage'' photography series pairs domestic tools with the naked female body.<ref>[http://lightra.com/front/gallery/40 \"AVANTGARDE PORTFOLIO SHOWCASE | MELANIE BONAJO | GALLERY\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160514020229/http://lightra.com/front/gallery/40 |date=2016-05-14 }}, \"[[Lightra]]\", Retrieved 7 April 2016.</ref> In 2012 she initiated Genital International, a feminist performance collective event about participation and equality. Bonajo's photography series and music video work ''Pee on Presidents'' is often tied to the recent anti-censorship and sex-positive branches of the feminist movement for its endorsement of female body agency in public environments, resulting in a provocation of censorship laws in the media.<ref>Frank, Priscilla. [http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/13/artists-respond-female-body-censorship-online_n_7042926.html \"15 Feminist Artists Respond To The Censorship Of Women\u2019s Bodies Online\"], \"[[The Huffington Post]]\", 13 April 2015. Retrieved 7 April 2016.</ref>\n\n==Current==\n\nBonajo released her first major publication since ''Spheres''<ref>{{cite web|title=Spheres #1 \u2013 Melanie Bonajo / In what spheres do we live in?|url=http://www.mottodistribution.com/shop/spheres-1-melanie-bonajo-in-what-spheres-do-we-live-in.html|website=motto distribution|accessdate=18 September 2016}}</ref> in December 2015 ''Matrix Botanica Nonhuman Persons'' designed by Experimental Jetset,<ref>{{\ncite web\n|title=This was 2015\n|url=http://www.experimentaljetset.nl/news/this-was-2015\n|website=experimental jetset\n|accessdate=18 September 2016}}</ref> which explores the ways we experience nature through representations on the internet, via YouTube and blogs posting adorable, funny or adorably sad amateur videos and photographs of nonhuman animals. This publication delves into the ways nature education has changed over the years and integrates the voices of animal behavior scientists rather than a National Geographic perspective.<ref>{{cite web|title=Matrix Botanica\u2014Non-Human Persons|url=http://www.becapricious.com/non-human-persons/|website=Capricious|publisher=Capricious Publishing|accessdate=18 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nAs of March 2016, Bonajo, along with curators Maaike Gouwenberg and Emma Panza, was shortlisted to represent The Netherlands at the 57th Venice Biennale.\n\n\u201cThe method of Bonajo is representative of practices of a younger generation that is based on collectivity and exchange.\u201d<ref>[https://www.mondriaanfonds.nl/2016/03/02/vijf-plannen-op-shortlist-nederlands-paviljoen-biennale-venetie-2/ \"Vijf plannen op shortlist Nederlands paviljoen Bi\u00ebnnale Veneti\u00eb\"] \"Mondriaan Fonds\", Amsterdam. 2 March 2016. Retrieved 7 April 2016.</ref>\n\nHer third ''Night Soil'' film to complete the trilogy premiered at the [[Tate Modern]]'s Artists' Cinema<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tate|title=MELANIE BONAJO: NIGHT SOIL TRILOGY|url=http://www.tate.org.uk/whats-on/tate-modern/film/melanie-bonajo-night-soil-trilogy|website=Tate|accessdate=18 September 2016}}</ref> in London  September 7, 2016.<ref>Tate Modern. [http://www.e-flux.com/announcements/2016-cinema-programme/ \"2016 Cinema Programme\"], \"[[e-flux]]\", New York. 1 January 2016. Retrieved 7 April 2016.</ref> It will then be showcased at Foam museum in Amsterdam starting September 15, 2016 as part of the Next Level exhibition.<ref>Foam. [http://www.foam.org/museum/programme/melanie-bonajo?gclid=CP7F04nNuc4CFdQaGwodDBAPKw] .</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Melanie Bonajo has been selected and shortlisted for the Prix de Rome Visual Arts 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://prixderome.nl/2017/04/20/shortlist-prix-de-rome-beeldende-kunst-2017-bekend/|title=Shortlist Prix de Rome Beeldende Kunst 2017 bekend|date=2017-04-20|website=Prix de Rome|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref>\n\n==Selected works==\n\n===Filmography===\n*2019 [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ExntKAxqarg TouchMETell] \n*2018 [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qf9FvCIlVn8 Progress vs Sunsets]\n*2016 Night Soil - Nocturnal Gardening \n*2016 [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KY_9ocvEi5M&t=57s Progress vs Regress] \n*2015 Night Soil - Economy of Love \n*2014 [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qpCxYSRgcLU&t=5s Night Soil - Fake Paradise]\n*2013 [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mafwxB0bEjQ Pee on Presidents] \n*2013 Matrix Botanica - Biosphere Above Nations\n\n===Discography===\n*2018 Melanie Bonajo - Single Mother Songs from the End of Nature \n*2016 Matrix Botanica - How to Escape from an Elderly Home Method 2016\n*2014 [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eO3pUE6QT5Y ZaZaZoZo - Woke up as a Wolf]\n*2013 ZaZaZoZo - Inua (Tsunami Addiction)\n\n===Photography===\n*2014 [https://vimeo.com/72429081 Pee on Presidents] \n*2012 How to get Closer to Nature Exercises \n*2009 Furniture Bondage [http://visualmelt.com/Melanie-Bonajo-Furniture-Bondage]\n*2008 Thank You For Hurting Me I Really Needed That (Crying Series)\n\n===Publications===\n*2015 [https://perimeterbooks.com/Melanie-Bonajo-Matrix-Botanica-Non-Human-Persons Matrix Botanica - Non Human Persons] (Capricious Publishing, designed by Experimental Jetset)<ref>{{cite web|title=Preview On Earth|url=https://issuu.com/foam-magazine/docs/08-102_44_fm44_on_earth_issuu_singl|website=Issuu|accessdate=18 September 2016}}</ref>\n*2014 Pee on Presidents, (Self Publish Be Happy) \n*2012 SPHERES, (Spheres Publications) <ref>{{cite web|author=Julia Kahl|title=Spheres #1 \u2013 Melanie Bonajo / In what spheres do we live?|url=https://www.slanted.de/eintrag/spheres-1-melanie-bonajo|website=Slanted|accessdate=2012-09-21}}</ref>\n*2012 [http://www.mottodistribution.com/shop/one-question-nine-possible-answers-three-rooms-1.html One Room, Nine Possible Answers, Three Rooms] (Self published) \n*2009 Volkerschau Zine (Capricious publishing)<ref>http://